name etex
category Package
revision 77830
shortdesc An extended version of TeX, from the NTS project
longdesc An extended version of TeX (capable of running as if it were
longdesc unmodified TeX). E-TeX has been specified by the LaTeX team as
longdesc the base engine for LaTeX2e. Thus, LaTeX programmers may assume
longdesc e-TeX functionality, along with additional extensions. The
longdesc pdftex engine and others directly incorporate the e-TeX
longdesc extensions. The etex program in most distributions is an
longdesc incarnation of pdftex running in DVI mode. The development
longdesc source for e-TeX is the TeX Live source repository, although
longdesc further extensions have taken place in the pdftex and other
longdesc engine sources, keeping e-TeX stable.
